  "diagnostic_ledger": [
    "The first canary exposed unusable zero latency samples because systemd-timesyncd reported synchronized while the three measurement hosts differed by more than 100 ms end to end; chrony against the Google metadata clock reduced observed offsets below 0.1 ms.",
    "One early 600-part track window missed one part; a fully cold rerun delivered all 4,800 parts and the miss did not recur.",
    "A back-to-back short-window ladder produced non-monotonic p99 because connection cleanup and churn carried into later tiers. Capacity tiers were rerun individually from fresh edge processes for ten seconds.",
    "The reader host remained below 40% total CPU during the broad ramp, including loads beyond the edge failure point, so it was not the capacity limiter.",
    "Every H3 handshake completed through 1,024 simultaneous track connections in the diagnostic ramp. The production ceiling observed here is request CPU/queue throughput, not a fixed global H3 connection count.",
    "DAW startup still creates 56 explicit erasure packaging errors while eight tracks register sequentially. Qualification windows start three seconds into the session and contain no erasures; startup track-map declaration remains a required reliability fix."
  ],
